name: fertilising, by broadcaster | fertilising, by broadcaster | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/27799/documentation

This dataset represents the service of fertilising broad acre crops over 1 ha of agricultural land. The fertiliser is assumed to be 30 metres wide and 125kW.;Dataset exchanges scaled from GLO parent dataset based on diesel consumption in Australia with other flows on capital infrastructure being kept the same as global process.;This inventory has been developed as part of the AusAgLCI initiative funded by a partnership of Australian Research and Development Corporations (RIRDC, CRDC, GRDC, SRDC, HAL, MLA, DA, FWPA) and Research Agencies (CSIRO, USQ and Q DAFF), with technical support from Life Cycle Strategies. More detail on inventory development can be found in the 'AusAgLCI Methodology for developing Life Cycle Inventory' documents located at www.Auslci.alcas.asn.au. Energy use from WA farm energy calculator.;Fuel consumption data have been derived from the Western Australia Farm Energy Calculator for broadacre crop.

Mineral fertilizing process starting from preliminary work at farm, like attaching the adequate machinery to the tractor.

This activity ends with transfer back to farm and concluding work, like uncoupling the machine. The dataset includes broadcasting solid mineral fertilizer or applying liquid mineral fertilizer over 1 ha of field, including field turning, idling and overlapping. The inventory takes into account the diesel fuel consumption and the amount of agricultural machinery and of the shed, which has to be attributed to the fertilizing. Also taken into consideration is the amount of emissions to the air from combustion and the emission to the soil from tyre abrasion during the work process. The amount of applied fertilizer is not taken into account, nor dust other than from combustion and noise.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/016:Support activities to agriculture and post-harvest crop activities/0161:Support activities for crop production

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Model is based on data in 2010
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Fuel consumption data have been derived from the Western Australia Farm Energy Calculator for fertilising from global defaults.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Fuel use is from current technology used in Australia
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Values given in the reference are representative for the chosen work processes. Dataset based on GLO parent dataset which was extrapolated from CH geography context without modification of exchanges. Processes are typical procedures for Switzerland around the year 2000, they are not statistical average processes. This dataset has been adapted only for diesel input representative of the Australia context and for combustion emissions scaled from the difference in diesel consumption. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data on fuel consumption and emissions of CO, HC and NOx are expert estimations based on measurements for comparable activities (rolling). The other emissions were calculated based on literature data and the measured fuel consumption.
